{{Infobox journal | italic title = force | title = APT Bulletin | cover = | editor = Diana S. Waite | discipline = [[Historic preservation]] | former_names = Newsletter of the Association for Preservation Technology, Bulletin of the Association for Preservation Technology | abbreviation = APT Bull. | publisher = [[Association for Preservation Technology International]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1969−present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.apti.org/publications/apt-bulletin-the-journal-of-preservation-technology/ | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = 08488525 | OCLC = 61236541 | LCCN = 93640569 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0848-8525 | eISSN = }} '''''APT Bulletin''''' is a quarterly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by the [[Association for Preservation Technology International]]. It is currently [[Editor-in-chief|edited]] by Diana S. Waite (Mount Ida Press) with the assistance of various guest editors. The content of ''APT Bulletin'' consists primarily of articles about the practice and technology of [[historic preservation]], but essays and [[Academic_journal#Book_reviews|book reviews]] are also included.<ref name="official">{{Cite web |url=http://www.apti.org/publications/apt-bulletin-the-journal-of-preservation-technology/ |title=APT Bulletin, The Journal of Preservation Technology |publisher=Association for Preservation Technology International |accessdate=April 27, 2014}}</ref>
==History== The journal began publication in 1969 as the ''Newsletter of the Association for Preservation Technology'' (1969), changing its name that same year to the ''Bulletin of the Association for Preservation Technology''.<ref name="official"/> The journal's title was shortened to the current ''APT Bulletin'', starting with Volume 18 in 1986. Publication is typically quarterly, although there have been several double issues.<ref name="jstor">{{Cite web |url=https://www.jstor.org/journals/08488525.html |title=APT Bulletin |publisher=[[JSTOR]] |accessdate=April 27, 2014}}</ref>
Guest-edited special issues of ''APT Bulletin'' have included articles on the following themes: the U.S. [[National Park Service]] (1978 and 1984), [[Parks Canada]] (1986), [[Guastavino tile]] vaults (1999), [[covered bridges]] (2004), [[Modern architecture|modern heritage]] (2011), and many others.<ref name="jstor"/>
