[[File:Jokipii in Eura 1992.jpg|thumb|Professor Mauno Jokipii presenting a meeting place of Iron Age in [[Eura]], Finland at 1992.]]
'''Mauno Jokipii''' (21 August 1924 – 2 January 2007)<ref name=uv>{{cite web |url= http://www.uppslagsverket.fi/sv/sok/view-103684-JokipiiMauno |title= Mauno Jokipii |publisher=Uppslagsverket|accessdate= 30 October 2016|language=sv}}</ref> was a [[Finland|Finnish]] professor at the [[University of Jyväskylä]] in history<ref name="ks">{{cite web |url= http://yle.fi/uutiset/professori_mauno_jokipii_kuollut/5756833 |title= Professori Jokipii kuollut |publisher= Yle News |date= 3 January 2007 |accessdate= 24 July 2015 |language=fi}}</ref> specializing in [[World War II]].<ref name=uv /> He was a thorough investigator and a prolific author. Among his works were studies of the local history of Jyväskylä and the university<ref name="jyu">{{cite web |url= https://www.jyu.fi/yliopistopalvelut/viestinta/yliopistonesittelyt/historia1.pptx |title= Seminaarista yliopistoksi – monikerroksinen kampus kertoo yliopiston vaiheista Esittelykalvoja. Jyväskylän yliopisto |language= Finnish |accessdate= 24 July 2015}}</ref> and [[Satakunta (historical province)|historical province of Satakunta]].

Jokipii was born in [[Helsinki]]. Jokipii attended [[University of Helsinki]] from 1952 to 1959,<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.helsinki.fi/kansatiede/histmaatalous/extrat/erillisartikkelit_maatalousmuseo.htm |last= Korhonen |first= Teppo |title= Sata Vuotta Maatalousmuseotoimintaa |publisher= University of Helsinki |accessdate= 2 January 2007}}</ref> and began publishing almost immediately (1954). He received his [[doctorate]] in Philosophy in 1957.<ref name=uv /> He was [[Dean (education)|Dean]] of the History-Linguistics department from 1960 to 1966.<ref name="ks" />

Although some of his early works had been noted, Jokipii sprung on the world scene with his 900-page study of the Finnish [[Schutzstaffel|SS]] battalion in World War II.  This study established a new level of detail in [[World War II]] military history.<ref>Hamalainen, Pekka Kalevi (December 1969) "Review: ''Panttipataljoona: Suomalaisen SS-pataljoonan Historia'' by Mauno Jokipii" ''The American Historical Review'' 75(2): pp. 521-522</ref> Jokipii's massive work ''The Continuation War: An Investigation of German-Finnish Military Collaboration 1940-1941'' firmly established him as a world scholar and moved the debate about German Finnish relations during World War II to a new level.<ref>Hamalainen, Pekka Kalevi (December 1989) "Review: Mauno Jokipii ''Jatkosodan synty: tutkimuksia Saksan ja Suomen sotilaallisesta yhteistyöstä 1940-41''" ''The American Historical Review'' 94(5): p. 1413</ref>

Jokipii died in [[Jyväskylä]].

